comments: Schroder (LAL) establishes himself in Green's (HOU) path and absorbs the contact.
Toscano-Anderson (LAL) jumps alongside Martin Jr.'s (HOU) path and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt.
Toscano-Anderson (LAL) turns slightly towards Smith Jr. (HOU) as he rolls towards the basket, and the contact is marginal.
Smith Jr. (HOU) brings his hands towards Schroder (LAL) and Smith Jr. absorbs the marginal contact as he firms up in Schroder's path.
Schroder (LAL) is moving alongside Green's (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Green (HOU) leaves his feet to pass and he returns to the floor while he is still in possession of the ball.
Westbrook (LAL) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two legal steps before his shot attempt.
After initially making contact with the ball, James' (LAL) hand brushes Gordon's (HOU) off arm and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Smith Jr. (HOU) brings his forearm towards James' (LAL) front and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Toscano-Anderson (LAL) places his hand momentarily on Smith Jr.'s (HOU) side and marginal contact occurs as they move in the same direction.
Brown Jr. (LAL) moves slightly forward towards Gordon's (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Brown Jr. (LAL) places his hand to Gordon's (HOU) side and marginal contact occurs as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Replay review of the foul called on Sengun (HOU) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Sengun (HOU) makes contact with James (LAL) that impedes his ability to pursue the rebound.
Schroder (LAL) and Green (HOU) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Martin Jr. (HOU) establishes himself in Brown Jr.'s (LAL) path and does not deliver contact.
Martin Jr. (HOU) brings his off-arm towards Toscano-Anderson's (LAL) vertical arm, and the contact during the shot near the rim is marginal.
Westbrook (LAL) initiates contact with Martin Jr.'s (HOU) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Schroder (LAL) cleanly deflects the ball away from Smith Jr. (HOU) during rebounding.  The ensuing contact to Schroder's head is caused by Brown Jr. (LAL).
Gordon (HOU) is moving alongside James's (LAL) path and marginal body contact occurs in transition.
Smith Jr. (HOU) brushes James' (LAL) arm and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Sengun (HOU) commits a take foul on Westbrook (LAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.

Replay review of the foul called on Schroder (LAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. However upon review, it was determined that continuation would not be granted and the foul was changed to a non-shooting foul. Schroder (LAL) grabs Sengun's (HOU) arm during the drive prior to his gather and the contact affects Sengun's SQBR.
Toscano-Anderson (LAL) and Smith Jr. (HOU) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
After initially making contact with the ball, Martin Jr.'s (HOU) hand slides off of the ball and onto James' (LAL) arm as he attempts to pass.
Schroder (LAL) is moving alongside Green's (HOU) path and marginal body contact occurs during Green's drive.
Green (HOU) brings his hand towards Schroder (LAL) and marginal contact occurs as Green releases away from the contact.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Green's (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Sengun (HOU) places his forearm to Toscano-Anderson's (LAL) backside as they come together and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
